"Mean is not zero, so the variables can be centralized. According to Janson and Wichern(2007),
when mu does not equal to 0, the mean-centered principal component y_i = e_i( x - mu) that has mean 0 and lies in the direction e_i. This can be done without loss of generality because the normal random vector X can always be translated to the normal random vector W =X - mu and E(W) = 0. However, Cov(X) = Cov(W)."

7. What is the final conclusion based on the previous methods?

ANSWER

For the original data set, QDA gives a lower misclassification rate in comparison with the LDA. PCA analyses before running QDA or LDA worsen the performance of LDA and QDA. That can be interpreted that a small portion of the total variance (recall we dismissed the least important 10% part of the total variance ) plays a vital role in classification.

After removing classes that are the hardest to distinguish, we see an important improvement in especially LDAs performance. WE can conclude that after removing those classes, building linear relations and classification based on that get easier. However, running PCA before QDA and LDA again ended up with high error rates. But this time, LDA seems affected much worse than QDA. We can interpret this result like loss of information damages LDA seriously.

In the alternative analyses that classes are removed for the purpose of reducing ambiguity in the data, we see PCA works much better with both LDA and QDA.

I wanted to recall that all these final interpretations are made based on the error rates for test data sets. It is obvious that there is an overfitting problem in the results of training parts.

Finally, in clustering analysis, in the Kmeans method cluster number is decided as 4, based on the elbow method, and to avoid any bias in comparison to different methods, the cluster number is kept the same as 4. Finally, for classes of 1,3,6, and 10, the K-means clustering method performs much better with adjustedRandIndex 0.39 than the hierarchical and model-based clustering method. To empower the algorithm learning, the training data set and test data set are merged at the beginning of the clustering analysis part.
